content.text:
Yes, exactly — but we need **both changes together**, otherwise it won't work.

**Why both are needed:**

The code flows like this:

```java
if (sessionId present && audType present && !isGuest) {
    // API call runs — sets audienceType from API response (WRONG for Internal)
} else if (equalsIgnoreCase(audType, "GUEST")) {
    audienceType = audType;  // Guest gets set correctly
}
// Internal falls through → audienceType stays null
```

If we only add Internal to the `else if`, Internal users with a `userKey` cookie will **still hit the top `if` block** first and get the wrong value from the API — they'll never reach the `else if`.

So the fix needs to be:

```java
// Change 1 — stop Internal users from hitting the API
if (sessionId present && audType present && !isGuest && !isInternal) {
    // API call — only runs for Customer/Partner now
}

// Change 2 — Internal falls here and gets set correctly
else if (equalsIgnoreCase(audType, "GUEST") || equalsIgnoreCase(audType, "INTERNAL")) {
    audienceType = audType;
}
```

Change 1 makes Internal skip the API. Change 2 catches them and sets `audienceType = "INTERNAL"` from the cookie. Both lines are needed. Want me to apply both now?

